summary:
Aleksandra specializes in social sciences and environmental policy development. She graduated from Wageningen University with MSc in Environmental Science , a major in Environmental Policy, and with a minor in Environmental Education. Main fields of interest are social studies and stakeholder collaboration on the implementation of new technologies in modern education systems.

Aleksandra has passion for the policy development process , and  cares about making leading a sustainable way of life.  She is a team-work person with problem-solving attitude. For now moment she is looking for entry-level position within NGO or a traineeship programme.

projects: [{'title': 'European Workshop-"Urban Green Spaces in Budapest"\u200b', 'date': {'start': {'month': 8, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}, 'end': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}}, 'description': 'This project was conducted by the group of 27 students from Wageningen University and commissioned by the Contemporary Architectural Centre (KÉK). During 8 week research students from Wageningen University worked on analysing current situation in Budapest in relation to the Urban Green Spaces. Research took place in 5 different districts in the city of Budapest .The main task of this project was to promote social cooperation and raise interest on bringing more green spaces in the city, and raising awareness of possible consequences of non-environmentally friendly attitude. This research required looking at the problem from different perspectives: political, social, economical, environmental and scientifically. The final outcome of the project is the synthesis report and presentation to the client (KEK) of the overall research done and possible ways to solve the current situation in Budapest.
